TITLE: Implementing HTTP Conditional GET with FusionCache in C#
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to implement conditional refresh using HTTP ETag headers with FusionCache. The code demonstrates checking for stale values, handling HTTP 304 Not Modified responses, and updating cache with new values and ETags.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ziggycreatures/fusioncache/blob/main/docs/ConditionalRefresh.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
var product = await cache.GetOrSetAsync<Product>(
	$"product:{id}",
	async (ctx, ct) =>
	{
		using var req = new HttpRequestMessage(HttpMethod.Get, $"/api/product/{id}");

		if (ctx.HasETag && ctx.HasStaleValue)
		{
			// ETAG + STALE VALUE -> TRY WITH A CONDITIONAL GET
			req.Headers.Add("If-None-Match", ctx.ETag);
		}

		using var resp = await client.SendAsync(req, ct);

		if (resp.StatusCode == HttpStatusCode.NotModified)
		{
			// NOT MODIFIED -> RETURN STALE VALUE
			return ctx.NotModified();
		}

		resp.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();

		// NORMAL RESPONSE: SAVE ETAG + RETURN VALUE
		return ctx.Modified(
			await resp.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<Product>(),
			resp.Headers.ETag?.ToString()
		);
	},
	opt => opt.SetDuration(duration).SetFailSafe(true)
);
```

